{
  "stem": "10181.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sternlager, yeah, yeah.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What was-- what happened in-- in-- in Bergen-Belsen was that-- you know where Bergen-Belsen's located, right?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's right in-- in the middle of North Germany, you know, it's--.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Eventually, more and more people came, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The-- like I said, the sanitary conditions never were good, but even so, at the beginning, the people managed to keep somehow clean.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the women, especially, would watch our-- us kids-- kids to make sure that we washed ourselves, you know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And as I said, the food at the beginning was like one slice of bread a day plus some terrible soup.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was something which looked like-- which was some dirty stuff which looked like coffee, which I didn't touch, of course, but I don't know what it was made of.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But whoever took it said it was awful.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The day-to-day life really consisted of roll call in the morning and going to work.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I didn't-- I said, I didn't in Bergen-Belsen-- most of the time, I didn't.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "A little bit, I did.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You know, there was a time when I worked in-- they were-- they were pulling soles of shoes from shoes, things like that, you know.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But most of the time, they didn't make us work, the kids.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They wanted us there at the roll call, which was, you know-- sometimes if the Germans were in a bad mood, you-- they would-- you would stand there forever, because nobody escaped or that I'm-- at least not from that camp-- nobody that I'm aware of.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Nobody escaped.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So the roll call really was just another form of-- of trying to-- to annoy you or upset you or whatever.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Another form of harassment, basically.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But when we arrived, of course, it was January, which was very cold.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Then the-- the spring started.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So it's always-- you always feel a bit better when the weather gets warm.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But then in the early spring or late-- it might have been later, May, June-- you know, as we were in the middle of Germany, the bombings were there, but not in Bergen-Belsen itself.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But we could see the-- you know, in-- in the sunny days, you could see the planes high up in the sky.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And in Bergen-Belsen, there was a crematorium, of course.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "There were no gas chambers, by the way, you know, but there was a crematorium where they burned the dead people.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And there was a factory nearby where they manufactured clothes for the German army.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I think they-- they-- from old rags or something, whatever.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And somewhere along the line, this was considered an important target.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And it wasn't attacked by bombs.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "It was attacked one day on-- out of the blue.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "It was attacked by fighter planes, you know, by-- by shootings.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I remember this very well because this was a big event, you know, because-- why do I say it was a big event?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, the camp was shot up too, at the same time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The crematorium went in flames.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The camp-- some people got killed, you know, by the bullets.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I always remember the sight of the-- the few German guards who were in the camp all of a sudden threw themself on the ground.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were scared.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't know what was happening, so I didn't [INAUDIBLE] myself on the ground.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, I'd never been shot at from the air.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then I-- and I found out, though, in-- in our barracks also, a couple of women, you know, got-- I know one woman got-- all the bullets must have gone-- must have gone through her.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then she was, you know, killed, and others were, too.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The other thing I remember in those days, something very interesting.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Like I told you, it was an-- supposedly it was an exchange camp at the beginning.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And these-- some of these Jews with a Palestine-- brought a certificate to go to Palestine were called.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was in June of 1944.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were called, supposedly to be exchanged, to-- to send-- be sent to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they were, by the way. 222 of them were called and put on a train.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And this I found, of course, years later-- made their way to-- to-- by train all the way across Europe through Turkey to Syria and made it to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And this was the only [? transfer. ?] And everybody thought, OK, this is the beginning.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Maybe we can get out of this hell-hole and go somewhere, maybe to Switzerland, whatever.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But this was the only exchange to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
